The paper deals with the problem of rectangle visibility representations of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of forbidden configurations and the study of 1-plane graphs suggest a connection to graph theory (cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT). The algorithmic aspect of the problem and the discussion of extensions suggest a connection to algorithms and complexity (cs.SI).
